  "title": "chore(typescript): setup Jest (part 1)",
  "body": "This is the first step toward our process migrating to TypeScript.\r\n\r\n- **Jest**.\r\n  - The Jest configuration has been moved to its own file.\r\n  - It upgrades Jest to version 24 (soon stable) which supports TypeScript by default. The Jest team seems confident enough to [use this alpha version in the React codebase](https://github.com/facebook/react/pull/14634), so I figured let's use it right now. Snapshots have been updated accordingly (a single file needed updates).\r\n\r\n- **Renovate**.\r\n  - The Renovate configuration has been moved to its own file.\r\n  - The `types` packages remain unpinned. The corresponding Renovate configuration has been created.\r\n\r\n### Related\r\n\r\n- Part 2: #3412\r\n- Part 3: #3413\r\n- Part 4: #3414\r\n- Part 5: #3417",
